<div class="modal fade" id="myModal13" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true" data-backdrop="static" data-keyboard="false">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-primary modal-lg" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h4 class="modal-title">General Fund Current Fiscal Year Enacted Budget</h4>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"> <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span> </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body" id="disclosure-allocation">
        <p><strong>Augmentation</strong> - Monies such as institutional billings or fees which are credited to a specific appropriation of State revenues. An augmentation can usually be spent for those purposes authorized for the appropriation which it augments. Although augmentations usually are appropriated in general terms with no specific dollar limits, Federal aid monies must be appropriated specifically.</p>
		  <p>All information based on transactions processed by the Treasury Department.</p>
		  <p>Fiscal Year refers to the time period of July 1 to June 30 of the given Budgetary Year.</p>
		  <p>Budget refers to the enacted budget bill for a Budgetary Year.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- /.modal-content --> 
  </div>
  <!-- /.modal-dialog --> 
</div>
<div class="modal fade" id="myModal14" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true" data-backdrop="static" data-keyboard="false">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-primary modal-lg" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h4 class="modal-title">General Fund Current Fiscal Year Enacted Budget</h4>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"> <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span> </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body" id="disclosure-allocation">
		  <p>Augmenting Revenue is monies such as institutional billings or fees which are credited to a specific appropriation of State revenues and is included as part of the total budgetary balance of that appropriation.</p>
		  <p>Revenue chart consists of all monies received from taxes, fees, fines, bond sales and other sources deposited in the State Treasury and available as a source of funds to State Government.  The received funds are categorized into account numbers which are directly associated with major classifications.</p>
		  <hr>
        <p><strong>Revenue</strong> - Monies received from taxes, fees, fines, bond sales and other sources deposited in the State Treasury and available as a source of funds to State Government.</p>
		  <p>All information based on transactions processed by the Treasury Department.</p>
		  <p>Fiscal Year refers to the time period of July 1 to June 30 of the given Budgetary Year.</p>
		  <p>Budget refers to the enacted budget bill for a Budgetary Year.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- /.modal-content --> 
  </div>
  <!-- /.modal-dialog --> 
</div>
<div class="modal fade" id="myModal15" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true" data-backdrop="static" data-keyboard="false">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-primary modal-lg" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h4 class="modal-title">General Fund Current Fiscal Year Enacted Budget</h4>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"> <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span> </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body" id="disclosure-allocation">
		  <p>Expenditures chart consists of all expenses linked directly to the listed appropriations of the current fiscal year’s enacted budget.</p>
		  <hr>
        <p><strong>Expenditure</strong> - As contrasted with disbursement, an accounting entry that is both the payment of cash and/or any encumbrance, as in accrual accounting.</p>
		  <p>All information based on transactions processed by the Treasury Department.</p>
		  <p>Fiscal Year refers to the time period of July 1 to June 30 of the given Budgetary Year.</p>
		  <p>Budget refers to the enacted budget bill for a Budgetary Year.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- /.modal-content --> 
  </div>
  <!-- /.modal-dialog --> 
</div>
<div class="modal fade" id="myModal17" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true" data-backdrop="static" data-keyboard="false">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-primary modal-lg" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h4 class="modal-title">Contracts e-Library</h4>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"> <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span> </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>Text</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- /.modal-content --> 
  </div>
  <!-- /.modal-dialog --> 
</div>
<div class="modal fade" id="myModal31" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true" data-backdrop="static" data-keyboard="false">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-primary modal-lg" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h4 class="modal-title">Treasury Checkbook</h4>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"> <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span> </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>Treasury, as an agency, processes approximately 208,000 payments during the course of the fiscal year as general operating expenses, federal and state mandated payments, Unclaimed Property claims, Tuition Account payments, and debt service obligations.  Expenses that meet publishing requirements according to the PennWatch bill can be searched for and displayed on this page.  Expenses that do not meet publishing requirements will be seen as “CHK Payee”, “WIR Payee”, or “ACH Payee”.</p>
        <ul class="check-circle">
          <li><em>Payments shown on this page are currently only Department of Treasury payments starting from September 23, 2019. </em></li>
          <li><em>Check numbers will not be provided.  The WarrantID can be used as a identification number. </em></li>
          <li><em>Processing time for payments will vary. </em></li>
        </ul>
		  <br>
        <h4>Payment Status Descriptions:</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong style="color:#dc3545 !important"><i class="fas fa-times-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> Cancelled: </strong> Your payment has been cancelled.</li>
          <li><strong style="color:#28a745 !important"><i class="fas fa-check-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> Paid: </strong> Your payment has been reconciled.</li>
          <li><strong style="color:#17a2b8 !important"><i class="fas fa-sync-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Processing: </strong> Your payment was received by Treasury and is processing.</li>
          <li><strong style="color:#ffc107 !important"><i class="fas fa-arrow-alt-circle-left" aria-hidden="true"></i> Rejected: </strong> Your payment has been rejected back to the agency department. Refer back to the agency department for more information.</li>
          <li><strong style="color:#007bff !important"><i class="fas fa-arrow-alt-circle-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Released: </strong>Your payment has been released to the US Postal Service for mailing.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- /.modal-content --> 
  </div>
  <!-- /.modal-dialog --> 
</div>
