      <div id="fund-info" class="col-sm-12 pt-2" >
        <h7>General Fund Balance</h7>
        <p>The General Fund is the state’s main operating fund into which the general
          (non-earmarked) revenues of the state are deposited
          and from which monies are appropriated to pay the
          general expenses of the state.</p>
        <p>The General Fund holds approximately 85 percent of total tax revenues and the majority of expenditures are transacted from this fund. This chart compares the actual General Fund balance, which includes the Short Term Investment Pool (STIP) line of credit advances provided by Treasury, to what the General Fund balance would be if the STIP had not been provided. </p>
